  "prompt": "Who are IAS Aspirants?",
  "response": "IAS aspirants are individuals who are preparing to take the Indian Administrative Service (IAS) examination conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) in India. The IAS is one of the most prestigious civil services in the country, and the examination is known for its rigorous selection process. Aspirants typically undergo extensive preparation, which can include self-study, coaching classes, and mock tests, to improve their chances of success. The examination consists of three stages: the Preliminary Examination, the Main Examination, and the Interview, and successful candidates are appointed to various administrative roles within the government.",
